title: For Sale:  Used (VG to EX ) 2 person 3 season USMC combat tent - Will Ship
postcontent:
Backpacking Tent, Hiking Tent, Combat Tent, 3 Season Tent, Military Surplus Tent, Prepper, bug out, Eureka, Diamond Brand, USMC, TCOP

Pictures of actual tent posted, Have multiple units available

Tent is military surplus so there is some wear, but overall very good to excellent condition. All zippers buckles tested and working and poles are straight. This unit includes 1 Tent, 1 Rain Fly, 3 Aluminum Poles, 8 Aluminum stakes, shelf netting and 1 repair kit.

The USMC Combat Tent is a two-man, three-season, free-standing, double wall tent. The Combat Tent incorporates a vapor permeable tent body with a waterproof floor and fly, which also provides 20 sq. ft. of vestibule area for gear storage. The Combat Tent has two doors (entrance/exit openings), and using shock corded poles, requires no special tools for erection and striking. Additionally, the rain fly is adaptable for use independent of the tent body as a "hooch", utilizing the poles provided. Set up in under 5 minutes

Technical Specifications:
Floor Area: 38 sq. ft. minimum
Minimum Weight: 8 lbs. 8 oz. (tent, fly and poles) 10 lbs. 6 oz. with repair Kit/Stakes
Height: 45" minimum at apex
Transport Pack Size: 0.5 cu. ft. (tent, fly, poles and repair kit)
Total Vestibule Area: Rain fly provides 20 sq. ft. of additional covered storage area
Rain Fly: Free-standing, reversible Camouflage Green and Desert Tan

Operable conditions 0° to 120°F
Ventilation for use in desert/arid environments, minimizes internal buildup of condensation
Withstands steady 40 mph winds and gusts to 55 mph
Provides protection from flying and crawling insects
Has sufficient head room for changing clothes
Rain fly covers all openings in the shelter
Rain fly prevents the escape of light and provides protection against visual and infrared
Rain fly when installed provides 20 sq. ft. of additional covered storage and is adaptable for use independent of the shelter
Rain fly has high wind guy out points for staking down the tent
Able to withstand 40 mph steady winds and 55 mph wind gusts
Protection from driving rain, sand and blowing snow
Rain fly and frame set up without the inner tent
Frame Poles. The frame poles are corrosion resistant Aluminum 7075 T9, Poles are connected together by means of cold weather shock cording.

Storage Bags.
Transport Bag is large enough to contain the entire tent and components.
Rain fly Bag is large enough to carry the rain fly, poles, repair kit, and stakes.
Repair Kit/stake Bag contains the tent stakes and repair kit.
Pole Bag contain disassembled/folded poles.

The concept in utilizing the transport bag and rain fly bag is to allow all of the components to be carried by one person in the transport bag or to allow two persons to carry all the components between the transport bag and rain fly bag.

title: For Sale:  Ruger LC 380 W/Lasermax Laser 380 ACP Pistol
postcontent: Ruger Reintroduces the LC380 Pistol to the California Market May 29, 2015 Sturm, Ruger & Company, Inc. (NYSE: RGR) is proud to announce the reintroduction of the Ruger® LC380® pistol to California. The LC380 was originally introduced nationwide in 2013 as a low-recoiling and easy-to-rack variant of the Ruger LC9® pistol. In 2014, Ruger made some minor changes to the LC380 production processes that would have required the pistol to meet California's controversial microstamping law. The LC380CA™ California compliant model reflects the unmodified pistol as originally approved by California in 2013.The Ruger LC380CA is a lightweight, compact pistol perfect for personal protection. The LC380CA holds 7+1 rounds of modern, effective .380 Auto ammunition in a slim, lightweight pistol. The pistol uses the same holsters and accessories as the rugged and reliable LC9 and LC9s®. The LC380CA also features a blued, through-hardened, alloy steel slide; a high-performance, glass-filled nylon grip frame with aggressive texturing; a finger grip extension magazine floorplate to improve handling; and a rapid acquisition, windage adjustable, 3-Dot sight system.The compact, 17.2 oz. Ruger LC380CA has a 3.1" barrel, an overall length of 6", a height of 4.5" and a slim 0.9" width. The compact frame and short trigger reach are designed to accommodate a wide range of hand sizes. The LC380CA offers modern safety features such as a tactile loaded chamber indicator, magazine disconnect, and a manual external safety. The LC380CA ships with one, 7-round magazine, a soft case and a cable locking device.As a special "bonus" with this reintroduction, the LC380CA will ship for a limited time with a LaserMax® CenterFire® frame mounted red laser.Later this year, Ruger plans to expand its offerings of Genuine Ruger Factory Parts & Accessories to include a 9mm caliber conversion kit for the LC380. The kit will allow owners of a Ruger LC380 or LC380CA to convert their pistol to safely and reliably fire 9mm Luger ammunition, providing added flexibility to shoot either lighter recoiling .380 Auto or more powerful 9mm Luger in the same handgun.For more information on the Ruger LC380CA or to learn more about the extensive line of award-winning Ruger firearms, visit Ruger.com or Facebook.com/Ruger. To find Genuine Ruger Factory Parts & Accessories for the LC380CA or other Ruger firearms, visit ShopRuger.com.

title: For Sale/Trade:  Taurus CT9 G2
postcontent:
Up for sale is a Taurus CT9 G2 rifle. Purchased it a little while ago, fired 50 rounds through it, then it has sat in my safe. No real need for it since I have other sub guns, so I figured I'd put it up to get a better home. You don't see these too often so I'll put in a bit more detail. 

This pistol caliber carbine is very tough and rugged compared to other out right now like the Sub2k and the Beretta. The polymer is a bit thicker and it uses more metal on the rifle itself than the other which adds to how robust it is. The rifle has a full length pic rail on top, which I've tossed on a red dot optic (which will come with it). The charging handle is located on the left and forward like the Bushmaster ACR, and does NOT reciprocate while firing. The trigger is aluminum and breaks at what feels like 3 - 3.5 lbs as well, very crisp and nice reset. It can be moved to the right side if you wish with a simple hex wrench. The safety is in the same position as an AR15, but it is a bit shorter. The rifle also breaks down very easily and quite similar to an AR15 as well, making this thing a breeze to clean. The rifle will also come with two steel magazines as well. No problem firing multiple types of ammo and it is rated for +P. I can be reached by email or text at REDACTED

title: For Sale:  Walther PP - 32ACP (7.65mm) - 2 Magazines & Soft Case - Magtech Ammo
postcontent:
This German Walther PP .32 is in nice condition. The deep black, high gloss bluing on the slide is excellent - the photos don't show this at all. I took the pics to best show the markings. There is slight bluing wear near the muzzle, and more obvious wear on the front and rear straps of the grip. The grip panels are in excellent condition. There are various nicks and slight scratches, some of which can be seen in the photos, but to see and hold the actual firearm it looks much nicer than my photos show.

I believe this one was manufactured in 1970, and was imported by Interarms. The Nds mark indicates it was a State Police (Landespolizei) of Niedersachsen issued firearm, formerly located in Lower Saxonia, West Germany. The antler mark on the barrel stands for the proof house in Ulm, Germany, where guns were sent for safety checks and must pass a pressure test according to German law. The eagle over N mark simply indicates it was Nitro proofed for smokeless powder.

Asking $450 face-to-face transaction. Includes 2 magazines and an Uncle Mikes soft case. For my asking price I will include 100 rounds of Magtech lead round nose .32ACP ammo.

I am in the Sewickley area NW of downtown Pittsburgh. I prefer to do transactions at Island Firearms on Neville Island. They have the cheapest transfer price in Pittsburgh.
